is unique immigrantcommunity plays within Ethiopian society.Rastafariare unusual among migrants, basing their movements on spiritual rather thaneconomic choices. This volume offers those who study the movement a broaderunderstanding of the implications of repatriation. Taking the Ethiopianperspective into account, it argues that migrant and diaspora identitiesare the products of negotiation, and it illuminates the implications of thisnegotiation for concepts of citizenship, as well as for our understandings ofpan-Africanism and south-south migration. Providing a rare look at migration to a non-Western country, this volumealso fills a gap in the broader immigration studies literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCitizenshipxSocial aspectsxEthiopia. 0aCitizenshipxSocial aspectszEthiopia. 0aEthnicityxEthiopiaxEthiopia. 0aEthnicityzEthiopia. 0aImmigrantsxHistoryxEthiopia. 0aImmigrantszEthiopiaxHistory. 0aPan-Africanism. 0aRastafari movementxPublic opinionxEthiopia. 0aRastafari movementzEthiopiaxPublic opinion. 0aRastafariansxHistoryxEthiopia. 0aRastafariansxPublic opinionxEthiopia. 0aRastafarianszEthiopiaxHistory. 0aRastafarianszEthiopiaxPublic opinion. 0aRepatriationxSocial aspectsxEthiopia. 0aRepatriationxSocial aspectszEthiopia. 7aRELIGION / Ethnic & Tribal.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071187540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479890996423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479890996.jpg  a978-3-11-071187-5  NYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13EN